description: The trend has been driven by rises in rents and house prices, with young people staying home so they can save for a deposit, according to a study from the Institute for Fiscal Studies.
title: Hotel of Mum and Dad! Number of youngsters living with their parents rises by more than a THIRD in two decades

description: Some 81 per cent of respondents said they regularly saw people 'excessively speeding', with 55 per cent saying there was a culture among UK road users that it was acceptable to speed.
title: Motorway speed limits are viewed as 'targets', 7 in 10 drivers admit - and more than half admit to going above them

description: Judges in a German high court are deciding whether the orthopaedic leather footwear, with its cork 'footbed', is so distinctive it should be protected alongside the country's other works of art'.
title: Will one-time 'dad shoes' be deemed a work of art? How ugly footwear of hippies and uncool dads could be protected alongside other works of 'literature, science and art' - including the Porsche 356 sports car and Bahaus chairs

description: Prince William was allegedly banned from his local rental video store during his time as a university student at St Andrews because he handed back films too late.
title: BlockBUSTED: Prince William was 'banned from his local video shop at university for returning films too late - as his VERY raunchy favourite rental is revealed'

description: The 33-year-old bank risk manager from Liverpool was sent packing after he lied to pals Minah and Frankie during the challenge, causing the other players to suspect him.
title: The Traitors viewers left 'devastated' after fan-favourite Dan was banished - with Linda narrowly surviving another Round Table
